        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- How to Use NBT Results -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>How Institutions Use NBT Results</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>
                Institutions use NBT results in various ways to support student success:
            </p>
            
            <FluentAccordion>
                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Admissions Decisions" Expanded="true">
                    <p>
                        NBT results complement NSC results in the admissions process. Institutions may:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use NBT scores as part of admission point calculations</li>
                        <li>Set minimum NBT requirements for specific programs</li>
                        <li>Consider NBT results alongside NSC for borderline cases</li>
                        <li>Use results for faculty-specific admission requirements</li>
                    </ul>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Student Placement">
                    <p>
                        NBT results help determine appropriate academic placement:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Placement in mainstream vs. extended curriculum programs</li>
                        <li>Identification of students requiring foundational support</li>
                        <li>Course selection and academic planning</li>
                        <li>Matching students with appropriate support services</li>
                    </ul>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Academic Development">
                    <p>
                        Results inform the design and delivery of academic support:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Development of targeted intervention programs</li>
                        <li>Design of bridging and foundation courses</li>
                        <li>Identification of students for early support initiatives</li>
                        <li>Resource allocation for academic development services</li>
                    </ul>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Institutional Research">
                    <p>
                        NBT data supports evidence-based decision making:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Predictive validity studies</li>
                        <li>Program evaluation and curriculum development</li>
                        <li>Student success and retention research</li>
                        <li>Quality assurance and institutional planning</li>
                    </ul>
                </FluentAccordionItem>
            </FluentAccordion>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Accessing Results -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Accessing Student Results</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>
                Institutions receive NBT results for students who have nominated them during registration. 
                Results are provided through:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Secure Online Portal:</strong> Access results for all nominated students</li>
                <li><strong>Data Files:</strong> Bulk downloads in CSV or Excel format for integration</li>
                <li><strong>API Integration:</strong> Automated data transfer to institutional systems</li>
                <li><strong>Regular Updates:</strong> Results uploaded within 4-6 weeks of test administration</li>
            </ul>
            <FluentButton Appearance="Appearance.Accent">
                Access Institutional Portal
            </FluentButton>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Understanding Results -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Understanding NBT Results</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            
            <h4>Performance Bands</h4>
            <p>Results are reported in three performance bands:</p>
            <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="12">
                <div>
                    <h5>ðŸŸ¢ Proficient</h5>
                    <p>
                        Student demonstrates competence that suggests academic performance can be expected 
                        to be adequate; students in this category are likely to cope with the demands 
                        of degree-level study.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h5>ðŸŸ¡ Intermediate</h5>
                    <p>
                        Student demonstrates partial competence in the area; challenges are predicted, 
                        which could be managed through access to special support such as augmented 
                        programmes, extended programmes, or additional tutorials.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h5>ðŸ”´ Basic</h5>
                    <p>
                        Student demonstrates a level of competence that suggests serious learning 
                        challenges will be experienced; an extended or augmented curriculum programme 
                        is strongly recommended, or foundation provision.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </FluentStack>

            <FluentMessageBar Intent="MessageIntent.Info">
                These bands are diagnostic, not prescriptive. Institutions determine how to use the 
                information based on their own context and student support capabilities.
            </FluentMessageBar>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Technical Information -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Technical Information</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>
                The NBT Project provides comprehensive technical documentation:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Test Construction:</strong> Information about test development and validation</li>
                <li><strong>Psychometric Properties:</strong> Reliability, validity, and fairness studies</li>
                <li><strong>Scoring and Scaling:</strong> How scores are calculated and standardized</li>
                <li><strong>Benchmarking:</strong> How performance bands were established</li>
                <li><strong>Research Reports:</strong> Annual reports on NBT research and development</li>
            </ul>
            <FluentButton Appearance="Appearance.Accent" Href="/resources">
                Access Technical Documentation
            </FluentButton>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Partnership and Support -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Partnership Opportunities</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>
                CETAP works collaboratively with South African universities to:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Conduct predictive validity studies at participating institutions</li>
                <li>Research academic development interventions</li>
                <li>Share best practices in student placement and support</li>
                <li>Develop new assessment tools and approaches</li>
                <li>Provide workshops and training for institutional staff</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                For inquiries about research collaborations, institutional partnerships, or technical 
                support, please contact us.
            </p>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- FAQs -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            
            <FluentAccordion>
                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="How do we register as a participating institution?">
                    <p>
                        Most South African public universities already participate. If your institution 
                        wishes to begin using NBT results, please contact CETAP to discuss participation 
                        requirements and data access procedures.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="What is the cost to institutions?">
                    <p>
                        There is no cost to institutions for receiving NBT results. Students pay the 
                        test fee directly when registering. Participating institutions receive results 
                        at no additional charge.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Can we conduct research using NBT data?">
                    <p>
                        Yes. Institutions may use NBT data for internal research purposes, subject to 
                        ethical clearance and POPIA compliance. For collaborative research projects or 
                        external publications, please contact CETAP to discuss data use agreements.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="How often are tests administered?">
                    <p>
                        Tests are offered multiple times throughout the year at venues across South Africa. 
                        This ensures students have multiple opportunities to write before application 
                        deadlines. Test dates are published annually.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="What technical support is available?">
                    <p>
                        CETAP provides technical support for data access, result interpretation, and 
                        system integration. Contact our institutional support team for assistance with 
                        portal access, data exports, or technical questions.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>
            </FluentAccordion>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Contact Section -->
    <FluentCard Style="background: #f3f2f1;">
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="12">
            <h3>Institutional Support</h3>
            <p>
                For questions about institutional participation, data access, research collaborations, 
                or technical support, please contact our institutional liaison team.
            </p>
            <FluentButton Appearance="Appearance.Accent" Href="/contact">
                Contact Institutional Support
            </FluentButton>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>
</FluentStack>
